text.tspan: The share of analyzed sequences in the preceding two weeks that correspond to each variant group. This share may
not reflect the complete breakdown of cases since only a fraction of all cases are sequenced.
Source: GISAID, via CoVariants.org – Last updated 12 March 2023
Note: Recently-discovered or actively-monitored variants may be overrepresented, as suspected cases of these variants are likely to be
sequenced preferentially or faster than other cases.
